<h2 id="section-top">Ophthalmology</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=939">East Lancashire Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>01282 803763</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContent82ac834a064f4e4cbdabb26f26508278">
</div>
<p>The department provides an extensive range of eye services for both adults and children.</p>
<p>We provide a range of services for all local residents and people from further a field who choose to be treated by our department.<br/>All our consultants are experts in their fields of ophthalmology and undertake all types of eye surgery.</p>
<p>They are all assisted by a team of doctors and nurses who all pride themselves on the delivery of the very best quality patient care.</p>
<p>Our main focus is the treatment and care of NHS patients with a wide range of eye problems, from common eye complaints to more specialized eye complaints which need expert care.</p>
<p>All planned surgery is undertaken at Burnley General Hospital in two dedicated eye theatres.</p>
<p> </p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>Ophthalmology services<br/>Ophthalmology treats conditions and diseases of the eye. This includes the anatomy and physiology of the eye and can include surgery and the diagnosis and treatment of eye problems including injuries and medical disorders. <br/><br/>Patients needing specialised treatment come from a wide area, and all the sub-specialities of ophthalmology are covered, including: <br/>Retinal surgery <br/>Medical ophthalmology <br/>Diabetic eye disease <br/>Glaucoma <br/>Paediatric (children) ophthalmology<br/>Treatments and services offered at the Ophthalmology services department <br/><br/>Service Delivery: <br/>Inpatient Elective (planned) - (Burnley General Hospital) <br/>Inpatient Emergency (unplanned) - (Burnley General Hospital) <br/>Day Case (same day service) - (Royal Blackburn Hospital, Burnley General Hospital and Rossendale Hospital) <br/>Outpatients - (Accrington Victoria Hospital, Royal Blackburn Hospital, Burnley General Hospital and Rossendale Hospital)<br/><br/>Contact Details: <br/>Opthalmology reception - Burnley General Hospital 01282 804186<br/>Opthalmology reception – Royal Blackburn Hospital 01254 734596<br/>Opthalmology appointments (new) – Royal Blackburn Hosptial 01282 803763<br/>Opthalmology Elective Admissions - 01282 803107</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
